Quote:  Tanker track troubles. Some North Taranaki dairy farmers say the Kiwi Dairy Company is taking a bullying approach over the state of tanker tracks on their farms. The farmers - who decline to be named because they say they fear retribution from Kiwi - believe the company's grading system for tanker tracks is overly rigorous. Acccording to the farmers, the company conducted surveys of tanker tracks and entrances, which included measuring track widths, turning conditions and entrances.
